  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "hObmchO51CVhd0sC93xENVDFxcE=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nA user's drives can be recovered on any device purely from wallet + Swarm \u2014 no server handoff.\n\n## Flow\n1. User opens Connect on a new device (served from Swarm).\n2. Signs in with wallet \u2192 derives encryption keys.\n3. Plugin reads the user manifest from the Swarm feed.\n4. Registers Swarm remotes for each discovered drive.\n5. `SwarmChannel.inbox` pulls all operations from per-document feeds.\n6. SyncManager applies them to the reactor \u2192 drive materializes in PGlite.\n7. Cursor is set; future syncs are incremental.\n\n## Why this works end-to-end\n- The wallet signature is deterministic \u2014 same wallet yields the same keys and same feed topics.\n- The user manifest is the single discovery root; from it the plugin walks drives \u2192 documents \u2192 batches.\n- No centralized account state is needed on any server.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"Flow 3: New Device Recovery (from Swarm)\".",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
